#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:333
msgid ""
"Signals that depend on an extension are hidden automatically if that "
"extension is inactive or there is not enough data. Response time and rate "
"thresholds are configurable below. Signals are omitted rather than estimated."
msgstr ""

#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:341
msgid "Response rate grace period (hours)"
msgstr ""

#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:342
msgid ""
"Conversations opened within this many hours are left out of the response "
"rate, so a brand-new unanswered message does not lower a vendor's rate "
"before they have had a fair chance to reply. Default: 48."
msgstr ""

#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:351
msgid "Minimum response rate to display (%)"
msgstr ""

#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:352
msgid ""
"The response rate is only shown when it is at least this percentage, so a "
"low rate is not advertised on the vendor's own page. Set to 0 to always show "
"it. Default: 80."
msgstr ""

#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:361
msgid "Slowest response time to display (days)"
msgstr ""

#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:362
msgid ""
"The response time signal is hidden entirely when a vendor's typical first "
"reply is slower than this many days. The displayed wording always comes from "
"the true value (within an hour, a day, a few days, a week, two weeks, a "
"month), so whatever is shown reads true at any setting. Default: 3."
msgstr ""

#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:371
msgid "Minimum conversations"
msgstr ""

#: build/hivepress-trust-signals/hivepress-trust-signals.php:372
msgid ""
"Response time and rate are only shown once a vendor has received at least "
"this many conversations."
msgstr ""

